---
const props = Astro.props;
const { data } = props;

---

<div id="region-details" class="my-8" >
    
    <!-- Accordion Container -->
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-8">
      <!-- The Political Weather -->
      <div class="accordion-item bg-white border border-[#FEE96A]/30 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
        <button class="accordion-trigger w-full px-6 py-4 text-left  bg-[#FEE96A]/10 hover:bg-[#FEE96A]/20 transition-colors flex justify-between items-center">
          <div class="flex items-center space-x-3">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" x="0px" y="0px" width="64" height="64" viewBox="0 0 64 64" stroke="currentColor" class="w-8 h-8 text-[#064161]">
              <path d="M 29 7 C 25.686 7 23 9.686 23 13 L 15 13 C 11.686 13 9 15.686 9 19 L 9 45 C 9 48.314 11.686 51 15 51 L 49 51 C 52.314 51 55 48.314 55 45 L 55 19 C 55 15.686 52.314 13 49 13 L 41 13 C 41 9.686 38.314 7 35 7 L 29 7 z M 29 11 L 35 11 C 36.104 11 37 11.895 37 13 L 27 13 C 27 11.895 27.896 11 29 11 z M 15 17 L 49 17 C 50.105 17 51 17.895 51 19 L 51 27.328125 C 47.860304 27.865386 40.276945 29 32 29 C 23.725715 29 16.142076 27.866066 13 27.328125 L 13 19 C 13 17.895 13.895 17 15 17 z M 13 31.384766 C 15.851521 31.855688 20.994182 32.574326 27 32.865234 L 27 33 C 27 34.105 27.895 35 29 35 L 34 35 C 35.105 35 36 34.105 36 33 L 36 32.917969 C 42.43805 32.665598 47.988855 31.881828 51 31.384766 L 51 45 C 51 46.105 50.105 47 49 47 L 15 47 C 13.895 47 13 46.105 13 45 L 13 31.384766 z"></path>
              </svg>
            <h4 class="text-xl text-[#064161]">The Political Weather</h4>
          </div>
          <svg class="accordion-icon w-5 h-5 text-[#064161] transform transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
          </svg>
        </button>
        <div class="accordion-content hidden px-6 py-4">
          <div class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-[#064161] space-y-4">
            <p>
              The 60s across South America wasn't exactly smooth sailing — coups, dictatorships, and Cold War puppet-strings pulled tight. The U.S. had its hands deep in the region, usually to stop anything smelling vaguely of socialism. That tension meant music wasn't just entertainment; it was also rebellion, survival, and in some cases, propaganda. Artists either leaned into government-approved "wholesome" sounds or used rhythm and poetry to slip messages past the censors.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- What People Were Hearing -->
      <div class="accordion-item bg-white border border-[#FEE96A]/30 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
        <button class="accordion-trigger w-full px-6 py-4 text-left bg-[#FEE96A]/10 hover:bg-[#FEE96A]/20 transition-colors flex justify-between items-center">
          <div class="flex items-center space-x-3">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-[#064161]" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 19V6l12-3v13M9 19c0 1.105-1.343 2-3 2s-3-.895-3-2 1.343-2 3-2 3 .895 3 2zm12-3c0 1.105-1.343 2-3 2s-3-.895-3-2 1.343-2 3-2 3 .895 3 2zM9 10l12-3"></path>
            </svg>
            <h4 class="text-xl text-[#064161]">What People Were Hearing</h4>
          </div>
          <svg class="accordion-icon w-5 h-5 text-[#064161] transform transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
          </svg>
        </button>
        <div class="accordion-content hidden px-6 py-4">
          <div class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-[#064161] space-y-4">
            <p>
              Before rock 'n' roll truly arrived, the continent was already grooving hard. Each country had deep folk traditions: Andean flutes, Afro-Caribbean percussion, Amazonian chants, gaucho guitar ballads — all feeding into urban life. In Colombia, cumbia (born from Indigenous, African, and Spanish roots) was already the people's soundtrack. In Brazil, samba had long reigned supreme, morphing into a slicker, lounge-friendly cousin: bossa nova. Argentina held onto tango but was also sneaking jazz into cafés. Basically, the continent had no shortage of rhythm.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Scenes & Sounds That Emerged -->
      <div class="accordion-item bg-white border border-[#FEE96A]/30 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
        <button class="accordion-trigger w-full px-6 py-4 text-left bg-[#FEE96A]/10 hover:bg-[#FEE96A]/20 transition-colors flex justify-between items-center">
          <div class="flex items-center space-x-3">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-[#064161]" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 10V3L4 14h7v7l9-11h-7z"></path>
            </svg>
            <h4 class="text-xl text-[#064161]">Scenes & Sounds That Emerged</h4>
          </div>
          <svg class="accordion-icon w-5 h-5 text-[#064161] transform transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
          </svg>
        </button>
        <div class="accordion-content hidden px-6 py-4">
          <div class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-[#064161] space-y-6">
            <p>This is where it gets juicy.</p>
            
            <!-- Brazil Subsection -->
            <div class="border-l-4 border-[#FEE96A] pl-4">
              <h5 class="text-lg font-bold text-[#064161] mb-2">Brazil</h5>
              <p class="mb-2">Bossa nova (or what i'd like to call OG Lo-fi music to study to) exploded out of Rio's apartments and beaches — João Gilberto, Antonio Carlos Jobim, Astrud Gilberto — smooth, jazzy, cosmopolitan. Later in the decade, Brazil's Tropicalia movement (Caetano Veloso, Gilberto Gil, Os Mutantes) mashed rock, psychedelia, and Brazilian folk into a technicolor protest soundtrack. MPB – Música Popular Brasileira: a broad label for sophisticated, locally rooted "serious pop." Jazz chords, samba swing, poetic lyrics.</p>
            </div>

            <!-- Colombia Subsection -->
            <div class="border-l-4 border-[#C13870] pl-4">
              <h5 class="text-lg font-bold text-[#064161] mb-2">Colombia</h5>
              <p class="mb-2">Cumbia went global. By the late 60s, it was traveling via records and radio, becoming a cultural export as much as a local favorite. Accordion-heavy vallenato also rose up, giving Colombia its second great pop sound.</p>
            </div>

            <!-- Chile, Argentina, Uruguay Subsection -->
            <div class="border-l-4 border-[#FEE96A] pl-4">
              <h5 class="text-lg font-bold text-[#064161] mb-2">Chile, Argentina, Uruguay</h5>
              <p class="mb-2">Folk revival with teeth. Nueva Canción took rural folk instruments and used them to sing about poverty, inequality, and resistance — Violeta Parra, Mercedes Sosa, Victor Jara. Music here became a revolutionary weapon.</p>
            </div>

            <!-- Peru Subsection -->
            <div class="border-l-4 border-[#C13870] pl-4">
              <h5 class="text-lg font-bold text-[#064161] mb-2">Peru</h5>
              <p class="mb-2">Rock 'n' roll got a tropical twist. Bands like Los Saicos arguably invented proto-punk with their raw, chaotic sound. Meanwhile, Peruvian cumbia (aka chicha) began blending Andean melodies with electric guitars.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- The Tech Factor -->
      <div class="accordion-item bg-white border border-[#FEE96A]/30 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
        <button class="accordion-trigger w-full px-6 py-4 text-left bg-[#FEE96A]/10 hover:bg-[#FEE96A]/20 transition-colors flex justify-between items-center">
          <div class="flex items-center space-x-3">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-[#064161]" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9.75 17L9 20l-1 1h8l-1-1-.75-3M3 13h18M5 17h14a2 2 0 002-2V5a2 2 0 00-2-2H5a2 2 0 00-2 2v10a2 2 0 002 2z"></path>
            </svg>
            <h4 class="text-xl text-[#064161]">The Tech Factor</h4>
          </div>
          <svg class="accordion-icon w-5 h-5 text-[#064161] transform transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
          </svg>
        </button>
        <div class="accordion-content hidden px-6 py-4">
          <div class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-[#064161] space-y-4">
            <p>
              The real game-changer? The electric guitar. Cheap imports flooded cities and made kids dream of forming bands. Add transistor radios, which carried global sounds into barrios and favelas, and vinyl records becoming more accessible. Studios were still relatively modest, but the fusion of folk instruments (charango, quena, bandoneón, cuíca) with modern kit (electric bass, Hammond organs, drum kits) created brand new soundscapes.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Notable Artists -->
      <div class="accordion-item bg-white border border-[#FEE96A]/30 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
        <button class="accordion-trigger w-full px-6 py-4 text-left bg-[#FEE96A]/10 hover:bg-[#FEE96A]/20 transition-colors flex justify-between items-center">
          <div class="flex items-center space-x-3">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-[#064161]" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M16 7a4 4 0 11-8 0 4 4 0 018 0zM12 14a7 7 0 00-7 7h14a7 7 0 00-7-7z"></path>
            </svg>
              <h4 class="text-xl text-[#064161]">Notable Artists</h4>
          </div>
          <svg class="accordion-icon w-5 h-5 text-[#064161] transform transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
          </svg>
        </button>
        <div class="accordion-content hidden px-6 py-4">
          <div class="space-y-6">
            <!-- Cumbia Section -->
            <div>
              <h5 class="text-lg font-bold text-[#064161] mb-4 border-b-2 border-[#FEE96A] pb-2">Cumbia</h5>
              <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
                <div class="bg-[#FEE96A]/10 p-4 rounded-lg border border-[#FEE96A]/30">
                  <h6 class="font-bold text-[#064161]">Los Corraleros de Majagual</h6>
                  <p class="text-sm text-[#064161]/80">Cumbia powerhouse, accordion-heavy party music.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-[#FEE96A]/10 p-4 rounded-lg border border-[#FEE96A]/30">
                  <h6 class="font-bold text-[#064161]">Andrés Landero</h6>
                  <p class="text-sm text-[#064161]/80">Called the "King of Cumbia."</p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-[#FEE96A]/10 p-4 rounded-lg border border-[#FEE96A]/30">
                  <h6 class="font-bold text-[#064161]">Lucho Bermúdez</h6>
                  <p class="text-sm text-[#064161]/80">Helped modernize Cumbia and spread it to urban audiences.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Bossa Nova Section -->
            <div>
              <h5 class="text-lg font-bold text-[#064161] mb-4 border-b-2 border-[#C13870] pb-2">Bossa Nova (aka "OG Lo-fi beats to sip coffee to")</h5>
              <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
                <div class="bg-[#C13870]/10 p-4 rounded-lg border border-[#C13870]/30">
                  <h6 class="font-bold text-[#064161]">João Gilberto</h6>
                  <p class="text-sm text-[#064161]/80">The father of Bossa Nova.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-[#C13870]/10 p-4 rounded-lg border border-[#C13870]/30">
                  <h6 class="font-bold text-[#064161]">Antonio Carlos Jobim (Tom Jobim)</h6>
                  <p class="text-sm text-[#064161]/80">Composer of "The Girl from Ipanema".</p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-[#C13870]/10 p-4 rounded-lg border border-[#C13870]/30">
                  <h6 class="font-bold text-[#064161]">Astrud Gilberto</h6>
                  <p class="text-sm text-[#064161]/80">Made Bossa Nova an international thing.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-[#C13870]/10 p-4 rounded-lg border border-[#C13870]/30">
                  <h6 class="font-bold text-[#064161]">Sérgio Mendes</h6>
                  <p class="text-sm text-[#064161]/80">Took the sound global with Brasil '66.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Tropicália / MPB Section -->
            <div>
              <h5 class="text-lg font-bold text-[#064161] mb-4 border-b-2 border-[#FEE96A] pb-2">Tropicália / MPB (Música Popular Brasileira)</h5>
              <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
                <div class="bg-[#FEE96A]/10 p-4 rounded-lg border border-[#FEE96A]/30">
                  <h6 class="font-bold text-[#064161]">Caetano Veloso</h6>
                  <p class="text-sm text-[#064161]/80">Godfather of Tropicália, radical and poetic.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-[#FEE96A]/10 p-4 rounded-lg border border-[#FEE96A]/30">
                  <h6 class="font-bold text-[#064161]">Gilberto Gil</h6>
                  <p class="text-sm text-[#064161]/80">Protest, poetry, and grooves.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-[#FEE96A]/10 p-4 rounded-lg border border-[#FEE96A]/30">
                  <h6 class="font-bold text-[#064161]">Os Mutantes</h6>
                  <p class="text-sm text-[#064161]/80">Psychedelic Brazilian chaos in the best way.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-[#FEE96A]/10 p-4 rounded-lg border border-[#FEE96A]/30">
                  <h6 class="font-bold text-[#064161]">Gal Costa</h6>
                  <p class="text-sm text-[#064161]/80">Iconic voice, blending Tropicália and MPB.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Nueva Canción Section -->
            <div>
              <h5 class="text-lg font-bold text-[#064161] mb-4 border-b-2 border-[#C13870] pb-2">Nueva Canción (Chile/Argentina, protest folk)</h5>
              <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
                <div class="bg-[#C13870]/10 p-4 rounded-lg border border-[#C13870]/30">
                  <h6 class="font-bold text-[#064161]">Violeta Parra</h6>
                  <p class="text-sm text-[#064161]/80">Folk matriarch, social voice.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-[#C13870]/10 p-4 rounded-lg border border-[#C13870]/30">
                  <h6 class="font-bold text-[#064161]">Víctor Jara</h6>
                  <p class="text-sm text-[#064161]/80">Protest singer, martyr figure of Chilean folk.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-[#C13870]/10 p-4 rounded-lg border border-[#C13870]/30">
                  <h6 class="font-bold text-[#064161]">Mercedes Sosa</h6>
                  <p class="text-sm text-[#064161]/80">"The voice of the voiceless" in Argentina.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- MPB Section -->
            <div>
              <h5 class="text-lg font-bold text-[#064161] mb-4 border-b-2 border-[#FEE96A] pb-2">MPB (Música Popular Brasileira)</h5>
              <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
                <div class="bg-[#FEE96A]/10 p-4 rounded-lg border border-[#FEE96A]/30">
                  <h6 class="font-bold text-[#064161]">Chico Buarque</h6>
                  <p class="text-sm text-[#064161]/80">Poetic, politically sharp songwriter.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-[#FEE96A]/10 p-4 rounded-lg border border-[#FEE96A]/30">
                  <h6 class="font-bold text-[#064161]">Jorge Ben</h6>
                  <p class="text-sm text-[#064161]/80">Funky, soulful, playful — later key in samba rock.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-[#FEE96A]/10 p-4 rounded-lg border border-[#FEE96A]/30">
                  <h6 class="font-bold text-[#064161]">Nara Leão</h6>
                  <p class="text-sm text-[#064161]/80">The "Muse of Bossa Nova," later a big MPB figure.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<script>
  // Accordion functionality
  document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
    const accordionTriggers = document.querySelectorAll('.accordion-trigger');
    
    accordionTriggers.forEach(trigger => {
      trigger.addEventListener('click', () => {
        const accordionItem = trigger.closest('.accordion-item');
        const content = accordionItem?.querySelector('.accordion-content');
        const icon = trigger.querySelector('.accordion-icon');
        
        if (content && icon) {
          const isOpen = !content.classList.contains('hidden');
          

          
          // Toggle current accordion
          if (isOpen) {
            content.classList.add('hidden');
            icon.classList.remove('rotate-180');
          } else {
            content.classList.remove('hidden');
            icon.classList.add('rotate-180');
          }
        }
      });
    });
  });
</script>


